  </equation>

  which gives only one real-constriant to <math|v<rsub|k>>. (but not enough,
  we need 4 real-constraints )

  At the same time, the eqn(5) will reduce to an eqn of <math|v<rsub|k>>:

  <\equation>
    <label|kmodeeqn>v<rsub|k><rprime|''>+\<omega\><rsup|2><rsub|k><around*|(|\<tau\>|)>
    v<rsub|k>=0.
  </equation>

  Furthermore, we hope <math|v<rsub|k>\<sim\>c
  e<rsup|-i\<omega\><rsub|k>\<tau\>>> when <math|\<omega\><rsub|k>> evolves
  slowly which aggrees with the case of flat spacetime theory (one-particle
  mode): <math|v<rsub|k>\<propto\>e<rsup|i k<rsub|0>x<rsup|0>>>where
  <math|k<rsub|0>=-k<rsup|0>=-\<omega\><rsub|k>>, from which we can uniquely
