  <section|Calculating the Power spectra>

  The power spectrums of perturbations and their spectrum-index \ can be seen
  from the cosmological observations which is valuable to test different
  inflation models.

  <subsection|Scalar perturbations>

  Physically, we want to know the spectrum <math|P<rsub|\<cal-R\>>> defined
  as the following

  <\equation*>
    <tabular|<tformat|<table|<row|<cell|<around*|\<langle\>|0<around*|\|||\<nobracket\>><wide|\<cal-R\>|^><around*|(|<wide|x|\<vect\>>,\<tau\>|)><wide|\<cal-R\>|^><around*|(|<wide|y|\<vect\>>,\<tau\>|)><around*|\<nobracket\>||\|>0|\<rangle\>>>|<cell|=>|<cell|<big|int><frac|d<rsup|3>k|<around*|(|2\<pi\>|)><rsup|3>><around*|\||\<cal-R\><rsub|k><around*|(|\<tau\>|)>|\|><rsup|2>e<rsup|i<wide|k|\<vect\>>\<cdot\><around*|(|<wide|x|\<vect\>>-<wide|y|\<vect\>>|)>>>>|<row|<cell|>|<cell|=>|<cell|<big|int><big|int><big|int><frac|k<rsup|2>
    sin\<theta\>d k d\<theta\>d\<phi\>|<around*|(|2\<pi\>|)><rsup|3>><around*|\||\<cal-R\><rsub|k><around*|(|\<tau\>|)>|\|><rsup|2>e<rsup|i
    k r cos\<theta\>>>>|<row|<cell|>|<cell|=>|<cell|<big|int><frac|d
    k|k><frac|sin<around*|(|k r|)>|k r><frac|k<rsup|3>|2\<pi\><rsup|2>><around*|\||\<cal-R\><rsub|k><around*|(|\<tau\>|)>|\|><rsup|2>>>|<row|<cell|>|<cell|=:>|<cell|<big|int><frac|d
    k|k><frac|sin<around*|(|k r|)>|k r>P<rsub|\<cal-R\>><around*|(|k,\<tau\>|)>>>>>>
  </equation*>

  where

  <\equation*>
    P<rsub|\<cal-R\>><around*|(|k,\<tau\>|)>\<assign\><frac|k<rsup|3>|2\<pi\><rsup|2>><around*|\||\<cal-R\><rsub|k><around*|(|\<tau\>|)>|\|><rsup|2>
